    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="321"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/8–1448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-14">August 14,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received August 14—1:19 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>340. Chairman student body Mukden Medical College arrested yesterday, charged
                    with leadership Tuesday protest meeting at garrison headquarters (mytel 428 to
                    Embassy yesterday<note n="49" xml:id="d321fn49">Same as telegram No. 339, <ref
                            target="#pg_415">p. 415</ref>.</note>). Declared guilty by garrison
                    commander at closed administrative trial; sentenced indefinite imprisonment,
                    “probably several months”.</p>
                <p>Unusual display police strength on streets. No visible student unrest.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking 429; repeated Department 340.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
